= OpenLaszlo Plugin
This plugin makes it easy to use OpenLaszlo applications with Rails.  It contains helpers and scaffolding that implement a variant of the REST API documented here[http://wiki.openlaszlo.org/Database_Connector].

For example, the 

Contacts is pre-alpha code.  See the "Unfinished Business" section at the end of this README for a description of some of the missing pieces.

== Requirements
 * Ruby -v of 1.8.2 (25-05-2004) or 1.8.3 
 * Rails 0.14.2
* {OpenLaszlo 3.1 or later}[http://openlaszlo.org]

== Installation
0. Install OpenLaszlo, Ruby, and Ruby on Rails.

1. Install the ROpenLaszlo gem:
  > gem install ropenlaszlo

2. Install this plugin.  In your rails application directory:
  > plugin install svn://rubyforge.org//var/svn/ropenlaszlo/rails/plugins/openlaszlo

3. Set your OPENLASZLO_HOME environment variable to the directory that contains the OpenLaszlo SDK.  If the following prints something, you've got it right:
> grep Laszlo "$OPENLASZLO_HOME/README.txt"

An example application that uses this plugin can be downloaded from here[http://osteele.com/sources/ruby/openlaszlo].

== Resources
